The paper deals with lower bounds for data structures that represent compressed strings and allow fast access to individual characters. This falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses reduction to communication complexity, which suggests that it may also belong to the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC) and information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper discusses lower bounds for specific compression algorithms such as LZ-compression and Burrows-Wheeler compression, which could place it in the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) or data mining (cs.DM).
